"MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "8", "role": "2,4"}]}, {"id": "R10", "infons": {"score": "0.9662", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D001647", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001647"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001647", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Bile Acids and Salts", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Bile_Acids_and_Salts"}, "role2": {"identifier": "MESH:D002784", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002784"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002784", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Cholesterol", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Cholesterol"}, "type": "Positive_Correlation"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "9", "role": "0,2"}]}], "pmid": 39780051, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-01T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Gut Microbes", "authors": ["Thibaut MM", "Roumain M", "Piron E", "Gillard J", "Loriot A", "Neyrinck AM", "Rodriguez J", "Massart I", "Thissen JP", "Huot JR", "Pin F", "Bonetto A", "Delzenne NM", "Muccioli GG", "Bindels LB"], "relations_display": [{"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Taurodeoxycholic_Acid|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Bile_Acids_and_Salts|@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, {"name": "treat|@CHEMICAL_tiadilon|@DISEASE_Atrophy"}, {"name": "treat|@CHEMICAL_tiadilon|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Bile_Acids_and_Salts|@DISEASE_Metabolic_Syndrome"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_tiadilon|@CHEMICAL_Cholesterol"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Bile_Acids_and_Salts|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, {"name": "positive_correlate|@CHEMICAL_Cholesterol|@CHEMICAL_Taurodeoxycholic_Acid"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Cholesterol|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, {"name": "positive_correlate|@CHEMICAL_Bile_Acids_and_Salts|@CHEMICAL_Cholesterol"}]}, {"_id": "39825851|None", "id": "39825851", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Epigenetics;2025Dec; 20 (1) 2451495. doi:10.1080/15592294.2025.2451495", "year": "2025", "type": "title", "authors": "Nicholls LA, Zeile KA, Scotto LD, Ryznar RJ, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Timing of dietary effects on the epigenome and their potential protective effects against toxins.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 98, "text": "Exposure to toxins causes lasting damaging effects on the body. Numerous studies in humans and animals suggest that diet has the potential to modify the epigenome and these modifications can be inherited transgenerationally, but few studies investigate how diet can protect against negative effects of toxins. Potential evidence in the primary literature supports that caloric restriction, high-fat diets, high protein-to-carbohydrate ratios, and dietary supplementation protect against environmental toxins and strengthen these effects on their offspring's epigenome. Most notably, the timing when dietary interventions are given - during a parent's early development, pregnancy, and/or lifetime - result in similar transgenerational epigenetic durations. This implies the existence of multiple opportunities to strategically fortify the epigenome. This narrative review explores how to best utilize dietary modifications to modify the epigenome to protect future generations against negative health effects of persistent environmental toxins. Furthermore, by suggesting an ideal diet with specific micronutrients, macronutrients, and food groups, epigenetics can play a key role in the field of preventive medicine. Based on these findings, longitudinal research should be conducted to determine if a high protein, high-fat, and low-carbohydrate diet during a mother's puberty or pregnancy can epigenetically protect against alcohol, tobacco smoke, and air pollution across multiple generations.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "humans", "locations": [{"offset": 182, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002241", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002241"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002241", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Carbohydrates", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Carbohydrates"}, "text": "carbohydrate", "locations": [{"offset": 520, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002241", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002241"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002241", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Carbohydrates", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Carbohydrates"}, "text": "carbohydrate", "locations": [{"offset": 1433, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "8", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000438", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D000438"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D000438", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Alcohols", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Alcohols"}, "text": "alcohol", "locations": [{"offset": 1525, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "4097", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [4097], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 4097, "biotype": "species", "name": "4097", "accession": null}, "text": "tobacco", "locations": [{"offset": 1534, "length": 7}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 39825851, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-01T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Epigenetics", "authors": ["Nicholls LA", "Zeile KA", "Scotto LD", "Ryznar RJ"], "relations_display": []}, {"_id": "40570323|None", "id": "40570323", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Organogenesis;2025Dec; 21 (1) 2519649. doi:10.1080/15476278.2025.2519649", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "PMC12258809", "type": "title", "authors": "Duan S, Zhang Q, Zhu J, Wang J, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "SS-31 Targets NOS2 to Enhance Osteogenic Differentiation in Aged BMSCs by Restoring Mitochondrial Function.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "4843", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55473", "valid": true, "normalized": [4843], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 4843, "biotype": "gene", "name": "NOS2", "accession": "@GENE_NOS2"}, "text": "NOS2", "locations": [{"offset": 14, "length": 4}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 108, "text": "This study delves into the rejuvenating effects of SS-31 on aged human Bone Marrow-Derived Mesenchymal Stem Cells (BM-MSCs), focusing on its potential to restore their diminished osteogenic differentiation capacity, a critical issue in geriatric medicine and bone tissue engineering. SS-31 significantly improved mitochondrial function, increasing ATP production by 35% and reducing ROS levels by 40% in aged BM-MSCs. Osteogenic differentiation was enhanced, as evidenced by a 2.8-fold increase in ALP activity and a 3.5-fold increase in Alizarin Red S staining intensity. Additionally, SS-31 reduced NOS2 expression by 50%, highlighting its therapeutic potential in age-related bone loss. SS-31 intervention not only normalizes mitochondrial structure and function, reducing ROS levels and enhancing oxygen consumption rates, but also targets the NOS2 gene, a potential drug target, which upon knockdown, leads to a substantial upregulation of osteogenic markers and an improvement in mitochondrial function. In conclusion, the findings of this study highlight the therapeutic potential of SS-31 in reversing the age-related decline in BM-MSC function by specifically inhibiting NOS2 expression and restoring mitochondrial function. This research provides a scientific basis for the development of new treatments for osteoporosis and other age-related bone diseases, emphasizing the importance of targeting mitochondrial function and cellular senescence in regenerative therapies.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "SS-31", "locations": [{"offset": 159, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 173, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "SS-31", "locations": [{"offset": 392, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000255", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D000255"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D000255", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Adenosine Triphosphate", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Adenosine_Triphosphate"}, "text": "ATP", "locations": [{"offset": 456, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "ROS", "locations": [{"offset": 491, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "470", "type": "Gene", "valid": true, "normalized": [470], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 470, "biotype": "gene", "name": "ATHS", "accession": "@GENE_ATHS"}, "text": "ALP", "locations": [{"offset": 606, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C004468", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["C004468"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "C004468", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Alizarin Red S", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Alizarin_Red_S"}, "text": "Alizarin Red S", "locations": [{"offset": 646, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "SS-31", "locations": [{"offset": 695, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "4843", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55473", "valid": true, "normalized": [4843], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 4843, "biotype": "gene", "name": "NOS2", "accession": "@GENE_NOS2"}, "text": "NOS2", "locations": [{"offset": 709, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001847", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001847"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001847", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Bone Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Bone_Diseases"}, "text": "bone loss", "locations": [{"offset": 787, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "SS-31", "locations": [{"offset": 798, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "ROS", "locations": [{"offset": 884, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D010100", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D010100"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D010100", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Oxygen", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Oxygen"}, "text": "oxygen", "locations": [{"offset": 909, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "4843", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55473", "valid": true, "normalized": [4843], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 4843, "biotype": "gene", "name": "NOS2", "accession": "@GENE_NOS2"}, "text": "NOS2", "locations": [{"offset": 956, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "SS-31", "locations": [{"offset": 1199, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "4843", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55473", "valid": true, "normalized": [4843], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 4843, "biotype": "gene", "name": "NOS2", "accession": "@GENE_NOS2"}, "text": "NOS2", "locations": [{"offset": 1288, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D010024", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D010024"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D010024", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Osteoporosis", "accession": "@DISEASE_Osteoporosis"}, "text": "osteoporosis", "locations": [{"offset": 1426, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019588", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019588"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019588", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Aging Premature", "accession": "@DISEASE_Aging_Premature"}, "text": "age-", "locations": [{"offset": 1449, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001847", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001847"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001847", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Bone Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Bone_Diseases"}, "text": "bone diseases", "locations": [{"offset": 1461, "length": 13}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [{"id": "R1", "infons": {"score": "0.9828", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D001847", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001847"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001847", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Bone Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Bone_Diseases"}, "role2": {"identifier": "4843", "type": "Gene", "valid": true, "normalized": [4843], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 4843, "biotype": "gene", "name": "NOS2", "accession": "@GENE_NOS2"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "0", "role": "19,16"}]}], "pmid": 40570323, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-01T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Organogenesis", "authors": ["Duan S", "Zhang Q", "Zhu J", "Wang J"], "relations_display": [{"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Bone_Diseases|@GENE_NOS2"}]}, {"_id": "40747836|None", "id": "40747836", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Ann Med;2025Dec; 57 (1) 2540598. doi:10.1080/07853890.2025.2540598", "year": "2025", "type": "title", "authors": "Wang Y, Meng J, Zhang J, Tian L, Wei W, Tang X, Zhang Q, Ding D, Wang X, Guo Z, He Y, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Cell biomechanics on muscle atrophy: from intricate mechanisms to therapeutic frontiers.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009133", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009133"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009133", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy"}, "text": "muscle atrophy", "locations": [{"offset": 21, "length": 14}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 89, "text": "BACKGROUND: Muscle atrophy-the decline of skeletal muscle volume and function-is pervasive in chronic disease, aging, and inactivity. As the primary driver of human mobility and metabolic health, skeletal muscle loss diminishes quality of life and increases healthcare burden. Atrophy impairs recovery and prognosis by reducing metabolic capacity, accelerating systemic protein catabolism, and compromising the biomechanical support necessary for movement and respiration. Although core molecular pathways and cellular changes are well characterized, the role of mechanical cues in modulating these mechanisms remains underexplored. MAIN FINDINGS: Our review reveals five convergent atrophy drivers-mechanical unloading, ECM alterations, mitochondrial dysfunction/oxidative stress, inflammation, and endocrine imbalance-that converge on inhibited mTORC1 signaling, activated FoxO/UPS/autophagy, and impaired satellite-cell function. Quantitative data show that axial stretch preserves PI3K/Akt/mTOR activity, with phosphorylated Akt levels increasing by two- to three-fold and fiber cross-sectional area expanding by 10%-20%; low-intensity compression activates AMPK and autophagy, with AMPK phosphorylation rising by 1.5-fold without triggering excessive protein breakdown; and shear stress enhances VEGF and Nrf2-mediated angiogenesis and antioxidant defenses, doubling VEGF expression and reducing ROS levels by 25% to mitigate neurogenic atrophy. Moreover, stem-cell myogenic differentiation is optimized on 3D biomimetic substrates with stiffness from 11 to 17 kPa under physiological loading, and advances in biomaterials and tissue engineering enable more accurate muscle-tissue models. FUTURE DIRECTIONS: Translating these biomechanical insights into tailored clinical interventions-combining stretch, compression, and shear modalities with biomaterials, stem-cell technologies, and personalized exercise programs- holds promise for preventing and reversing muscle atrophy across diverse patient populations.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009133", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009133"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009133", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy"}, "text": "Muscle atrophy", "locations": [{"offset": 101, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 248, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009135", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009135"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009135", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Diseases"}, "text": "muscle loss", "locations": [{"offset": 294, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001284", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001284"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001284", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Atrophy"}, "text": "Atrophy", "locations": [{"offset": 366, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001284", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001284"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001284", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Atrophy"}, "text": "atrophy", "locations": [{"offset": 772, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D028361", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D028361"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D028361", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Mitochondrial Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Mitochondrial_Diseases"}, "text": "mitochondrial dysfunction", "locations": [{"offset": 827, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D007249"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D007249", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Inflammation", "accession": "@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, "text": "inflammation", "locations": [{"offset": 871, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "5291", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "21250", "valid": true, "normalized": [5291], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 5291, "biotype": "gene", "name": "PIK3CB", "accession": "@GENE_PIK3CB"}, "text": "PI3K", "locations": [{"offset": 1074, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "207", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3785", "valid": true, "normalized": [207], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 207, "biotype": "gene", "name": "AKT1", "accession": "@GENE_AKT1"}, "text": "Akt", "locations": [{"offset": 1079, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "2475", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3637", "valid": true, "normalized": [2475], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 2475, "biotype": "gene", "name": "MTOR", "accession": "@GENE_MTOR"}, "text": "mTOR", "locations": [{"offset": 1083, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"id