SE_Liver_Failure|@GENE_DBI"}, {"name": "cause|@CHEMICAL_Benzodiazepines|@DISEASE_Carcinoma_Hepatocellular"}, {"name": "interact|@CHEMICAL_Benzodiazepines|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor"}, {"name": "treat|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@DISEASE_Liver_Diseases"}, {"name": "interact|@CHEMICAL_Benzodiazepines|@GENE_DBI"}, {"name": "cause|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@DISEASE_Carcinoma_Hepatocellular"}, {"name": "stimulate|@DISEASE_Carcinoma_Hepatocellular|@GENE_DBI"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@DISEASE_Cardiovascular_Diseases"}, {"name": "negative_correlate|@CHEMICAL_Carbon_Tetrachloride|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor"}, {"name": "cause|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@DISEASE_Osteoarthritis"}, {"name": "cause|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@DISEASE_Liver_Cirrhosis"}, {"name": "cause|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@DISEASE_Metabolic_Syndrome"}, {"name": "negative_correlate|@CHEMICAL_Diazepam_Binding_Inhibitor|@GENE_DBI"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Carcinoma_Hepatocellular|@GENE_MYC"}]}, {"_id": "41315622|None", "id": "41315622", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Sci Rep;2025Nov28. doi:10.1038/s41598-025-28645-8", "year": "2025", "type": "title", "authors": "Romien R, Pierre A, Ducastel S, Dubech A, Lemaire J, Grolaux G, Frimat M, Brassart B, Bourel C, Howsam M, Yelnik C, Boulanger E, Favory R, Preau S, Lancel S, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "RAGE contributes to persistent sepsis-induced muscle and mitochondrial alterations.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "11596", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "883", "valid": true, "normalized": [11596], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 11596, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Ager", "accession": "@GENE_AGER"}, "text": "RAGE", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018805", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D018805"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D018805", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sepsis", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sepsis"}, "text": "sepsis", "locations": [{"offset": 31, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D028361", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D028361"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D028361", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Mitochondrial Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Mitochondrial_Diseases"}, "text": "mitochondrial alterations", "locations": [{"offset": 57, "length": 25}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 84, "text": "A majority of patients surviving sepsis develop muscle weakness. However, the underlying cellular and molecular pathways remain largely unexplored. To determine whether sepsis leads to long-term persistent muscular consequences and to identify the underlying mechanisms, we used a murine model of reanimated sepsis induced by intraperitoneal injection of a heterologous stool slurry. Muscles were analyzed 3 months later. The oxidative muscle exhibited reduced fatigue resistance and decreased mitochondrial respiration, without a corresponding reduction in mitochondrial OXPHOS proteins. Glycolytic and mixed muscle fibres were atrophied. Markers of oxidative and mitochondrial stress, as well as genes involved in mitochondrial fission, remained present 3 months after sepsis. Low-grade, but significant, muscular inflammation was also measured. Specifically, both the NLRP3 inflammasome and the receptor of Advanced Glycation End-products (RAGE) axis were upregulated. Interestingly, long-term sepsis-induced muscular consequences were not observed in RAGE knockout mice. Overall, we describe for the first time in mice that sepsis causes long-lasting muscle dysfunction after recovery, including mitochondrial alterations and low-grade inflammation, and that RAGE may represent a promising target to mitigate long-term muscle alterations induced by sepsis.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "patients", "locations": [{"offset": 98, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018805", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D018805"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D018805", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sepsis", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sepsis"}, "text": "sepsis", "locations": [{"offset": 117, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018908", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D018908"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D018908", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscle Weakness", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscle_Weakness"}, "text": "muscle weakness", "locations": [{"offset": 132, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018805", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D018805"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D018805", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sepsis", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sepsis"}, "text": "sepsis", "locations": [{"offset": 253, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "murine", "locations": [{"offset": 365, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018805", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D018805"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D018805", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sepsis", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sepsis"}, "text": "sepsis", "locations": [{"offset": 392, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "40", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005221", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005221"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005221", "biotype": "disease", "name": "