ations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 120, "text": "Despite the beneficial impact of bariatric surgery on obesity and metabolic disease, continued post-surgical obesity and weight recurrence are common, but may be impacted by diet. While guidelines recommend a post-operative high-protein diet to preserve lean mass, emerging evidence suggests that humans and mice are metabolically healthier on low-protein diets. Here, we assess the effect of varying dietary protein on post-surgical metabolism in a mouse model of sleeve gastrectomy. We find that a low-protein diet optimally drives post-surgical weight loss, boosts energy expenditure, and improves blood glucose regulation, likely, in part, due to the induction of FGF21. Through multi-omics, we identified clusters of differentially expressed genes and metabolites that correlate with these phenotypes and find that diet heavily influences the liver's molecular response to sleeve gastrectomy. These results suggest that current post-surgical high-protein diets may limit the short- and long-term benefits of surgery and warrant human clinical trials.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009765", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009765"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009765", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Obesity", "accession": "@DISEASE_Obesity"}, "text": "obesity", "locations": [{"offset": 174, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008659", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008659"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008659", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Metabolic Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Metabolic_Diseases"}, "text": "metabolic disease", "locations": [{"offset": 186, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009765", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009765"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009765", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Obesity", "accession": "@DISEASE_Obesity"}, "text": "obesity", "locations": [{"offset": 229, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "humans", "locations": [{"offset": 417, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "mice", "locations": [{"offset": 428, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "mouse", "locations": [{"offset": 570, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"type": "Disease", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "disease"}, "text": "sleeve", "locations": [{"offset": 585, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D015431", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D015431"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D015431", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Weight Loss", "accession": "@DISEASE_Weight_Loss"}, "text": "weight loss", "locations": [{"offset": 668, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001786", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001786"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001786", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Blood Glucose", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Blood_Glucose"}, "text": "blood glucose", "locations": [{"offset": 721, "length": 13}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "56636", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "10428", "valid": true, "normalized": [56636], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 56636, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Fgf21", "accession": "@GENE_FGF21"}, "text": "FGF21", "locations": [{"offset": 788, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"type": "Disease", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "disease"}, "text": "sleeve", "locations": [{"offset": 998, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 1153, "length": 5}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 41330377, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-01T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Cell Rep Med", "authors": ["Illiano J", "Green CL", "Chao A", "Zhu G", "Lopez L", "Schaepkens O", "Jang C", "Lamming DW", "Harris DA"], "relations_display": []}, {"_id": "41331693|None", "id": "41331693", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Stem Cell Res Ther;2025Dec02. doi:10.1186/s13287-025-04841-1", "year": "2025", "type": "title", "authors": "Yu G, Chen Y, Li K, Qi L, Wang L, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Umbilical cord mesenchymal stromal cells in sarcopenia: benefits and strategies for enhancing efficacy.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 44, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 104, "text": "Sarcopenia is a progressive age-related condition characterized by the decline of skeletal muscle mass and function. Its development involves multiple cellular and molecular mechanisms, including chronic inflammation, apoptosis, mitochondrial dysfunction, and impaired muscle regeneration. Human umbilical cord mesenchymal stromal cells (HUC-MSCs) have emerged as a promising therapeutic strategy due to their potent immunomodulatory properties, paracrine effects, and ability to promote tissue repair. The regenerative potential of HUC-MSCs is largely mediated by the secretion of bioactive factors that suppress apoptosis, attenuate inflammation, enhance angiogenesis, and remodel the extracellular matrix, thereby establishing a microenvironment conducive to muscle regeneration. Nevertheless, challenges such as limited cell survival, differentiation efficiency, and long-term integration within host muscle, as well as variability in cell sources, delivery routes, and host immune responses, continue to constrain their clinical translation. In this review, we systematically summarize the biological characteristics of HUC-MSCs, their interactions with inflammatory and catabolic pathways in atrophic muscle, and their regulation of key signaling mechanisms involved in muscle repair. We also discuss current limitations and highlight future strategies-such as cellular preconditioning, biomaterial-assisted delivery systems, optimized transplantation protocols, and emerging organ-on-a-chip technologies-to enhance therapeutic efficacy and accelerate clinical application.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "Sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 104, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D007249"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D007249", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Inflammation", "accession": "@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, "text": "chronic inflammation", "locations": [{"offset": 300, "length": 20}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D028361", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D028361"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D028361", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Mitochondrial Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Mitochondrial_Diseases"}, "text": "mitochondrial dysfunction", "locations": [{"offset": 333, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019042", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019042"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019042", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscle Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscle_Neoplasms"}, "text": "muscle regeneration", "locations": [{"offset": 373, "length": 19}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "Human", "locations": [{"offset": 394, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "CVCL:3798", "type": "CellLine", "valid": true, "normalized": ["3798"], "database": "cvcl", "normalized_id": "3798", "biotype": "cellline", "name": "3798", "accession": null}, "text": "HUC", "locations": [{"offset": 442, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "CVCL:3798", "type": "CellLine", "valid": true, "normalized": ["3798"], "database": "cvcl", "normalized_id": "3798", "biotype": "cellline", "name": "3798", "accession": null}, "text": "HUC", "locations": [{"offset": 637, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D007249"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D007249", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Inflammation", "accession": "@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, "text": "inflammation", "locations": [{"offset": 739, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019042", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019042"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019042", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscle Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscle_Neoplasms"}, "text": "muscle regeneration", "locations": [{"offset": 866, "length": 19}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "CVCL:3798", "type": "CellLine", "valid": true, "normalized": ["3798"], "database": "cvcl", "normalized_id": "3798", "biotype": "cellline", "name": "3798", "accession": null}, "text": "HUC", "locations": [{"offset": 1229, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D007249"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D007249", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Inflammation", "accession": "@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, "text": "inflammatory", "locations": [{"offset": 1263, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D020966", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D020966"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D020966", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Disorders Atrophic", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Disorders_Atrophic"}, "text": "atrophic muscle", "locations": [{"offset": 1302, "length": 15}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 41331693, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-02T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Stem Cell Res Ther", "authors": ["Yu G", "Chen Y", "Li K", "Qi L", "Wang L"], "relations_display": []}, {"_id": "41335283|None", "id": "41335283", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Bioresour Bioprocess;2025Dec03; 12 (1) 141. doi:10.1186/s40643-025-00970-w", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "PMC12675900", "type": "title", "authors": "Jeyachandran S, Aman M, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Valorisation of fish scales and bones: a sustainable source of bioactive proteins and collagen for nutraceuticals.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 115, "text": "Fish scales and bones, traditionally regarded as low-value seafood by-products, represent abundant and sustainable sources of collagen and bioactive proteins with high nutraceutical potential. These tissues typically contain 30-40% organic collagen matrix and 60-70% hydroxyapatite minerals, making them rich substrates for recovery. Advances in green and enzymatic extraction methods now achieve collagen yields of up to 25-35%, with ultrasound- and microwave-assisted extraction reducing processing times from days to minutes while preserving the triple-helix structure and bioactivity. Enzymatically derived peptides demonstrate potent health-promoting effects, with antioxidant capacities comparable to or exceeding vitamins C and E, ACE-inhibitory peptides lowering blood pressure in preclinical models, and clinical trials showing that daily supplementation with 10 g fish collagen peptides for 8-12 weeks improves skin hydration, elasticity, wrinkle reduction, and reduces osteoarthritis-related joint pain. These marine biomolecules, when delivered through advanced nanocarrier systems such as nanoliposomes and nanoemulsions, exhibit enhanced bioavailability, stability, and consumer acceptability. Beyond health benefits, valorisation of fish by-products supports environmental sustainability by diverting waste and contributing to the circular bioeconomy. Despite challenges in scalability, regulatory compliance, and standardization, ongoing technological innovations position fish scales and bones as promising raw materials for next-generation nutraceuticals.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D017886", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D017886"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D017886", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Durapatite", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Durapatite"}, "text": "hydroxyapatite", "locations": [{"offset": 382, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "vitamins C and E", "locations": [{"offset": 835, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "163", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "68176", "valid": true, "normalized": [163], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 163, "biotype": "gene", "name": "AP2B1", "accession": "@GENE_AP2B1"}, "text": "ACE", "locations": [{"offset": 853, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "8", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D010003", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D010003"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D010003", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Osteoarthritis", "accession": "@DISEASE_Osteoarthritis"}, "text": "osteoarthritis", "locations": [{"offset": 1095, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "9", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D018771", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D018771"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D018771", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Arthralgia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Arthralgia"}, "text": "joint pain", "locations": [{"offset": 1118, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 41335283, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-03T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Bioresour Bioprocess", "authors": ["Jeyachandran S", "Aman M"], "relations_display": []}, {"_id": "41339969|None", "id": "41339969", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Nat Metab;2025Dec03. doi:10.1038/s42255-025-01412-9", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "7803748", "type": "title", "authors": "Santiago-Fern&#xe1;ndez O, Coletto L, Tasset I, Kaushik S, Concepcion AR, Qaisar R, Macho-Gonz&#xe1;lez A, Lindenau K, Diaz A, Khawaja RR, Donega S, Banskota N, Ubaida-Mohien C, Pharaoh G, Ahn B, Hartnell LM, Ram&#xed;rez-Pardo I, Chavda B, Gazteluiturri A, Kinter M, Ferrucci L, Reisz JA, D'Alessandro A, Van Remmen H, Mu&#xf1;oz-C&#xe1;noves P, Feske S, Cuervo AM, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Age-related decline of chaperone-mediated autophagy in skeletal muscle leads to progressive myopathy.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "1", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009135", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009135"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009135", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Diseases"}, "text": "myopathy", "locations": [{"offset": 92, "length": 8}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 102, "text": "Chaperone-mediated autophagy (CMA) contributes to proteostasis maintenance by selectively degrading a subset of proteins in lysosomes. CMA declines with age in most tissues, including skeletal muscle. However, the role of CMA in skeletal muscle and the consequences of its decline remain poorly understood. Here we demonstrate that CMA regulates skeletal muscle function. We show that CMA is upregulated in skeletal muscle in response to starvation, exercise and tissue repair, but declines in ageing and obesity. Using a muscle-specific CMA-deficient mouse model, we show that CMA loss leads to progressive myopathy, including reduced muscle force and degenerative myofibre features. Comparative proteomic analyses reveal CMA-dependent changes in the mitochondrial proteome and identify the sarcoplasmic-endoplasmic reticulum Ca2+-ATPase (SERCA) as a CMA substrate. Impaired SERCA turnover in CMA-deficient skeletal muscle is associated with defective calcium (Ca2+) storage and dysregulated Ca2+ dynamics. We confirm that CMA is also downregulated with age in human skeletal muscle. Remarkably, genetic upregulation of CMA activity in old mice partially ameliorates skeletal muscle ageing phenotypes. Together, our work highlights the contribution of CMA to skeletal muscle homoeostasis and myofibre integrity.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009765", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009765"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009765", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Obesity", "accession": "@DISEASE_Obesity"}, "text": "obesity", "locations": [{"offset": 607, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C564093", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["C564093"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "C564093", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Myopathy X-Linked with Excessive Autophagy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Myopathy_X_Linked_with_Excessive_Autophagy"}, "text": "CMA-deficient", "locations": [{"offset": 640, "length": 13}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "mouse", "locations": [{"offset": 654, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009135", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009135"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009135", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Diseases"}, "text": "myopathy", "locations": [{"offset": 710, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C564093", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["C564093"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "C564093", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Myopathy X-Linked with Excessive Autophagy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Myopathy_X_Linked_with_Excessive_Autophagy"}, "text": "CMA-deficient skeletal muscle", "locations": [{"offset": 996, "length": 29}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002118", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002118"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002118", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Calcium", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Calcium"}, "text": "calcium", "locations": [{"offset": 1055, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "Ca2+", "locations": [{"offset": 1064, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "Ca2+", "locations": [{"offset": 1095, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 1164, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "mice", "locations": [{"offset": 1243, "length": 4}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [{"id": "R1", "infons": {"score": "0.9985", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D002118", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002118"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002118", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Calcium", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Calcium"}, "role2": {"identifier": "MESH:C564093", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["C564093"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "C564093", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Myopathy X-Linked with Excessive Autophagy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Myopathy_X_Linked_with_Excessive_Autophagy"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "0", "role": "6,5"}]}], "pmid": 41339969, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-12-03T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Nat Metab", "authors": ["Santiago-Fernández O", "Coletto L", "Tasset I", "Kaushik S", "Concepcion AR", "Qaisar R", "Macho-González A", "Lindenau K", "Diaz A", "Khawaja RR", "Donega S", "Banskota N", "Ubaida-Mohien C", "Pharaoh G", "Ahn B", "Hartnell LM", "Ramírez-Pardo I", "Chavda B", "Gazteluiturri A", "Kinter M", "Ferrucci L", "Reisz JA", "D'Alessandro A", "Van Remmen H", "Muñoz-Cánoves P", "Feske S", "Cuervo AM"], "relations_display": [{"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Calcium|@DISEASE_Myopathy_X_Linked_with_Excessive_Autophagy"}]}, {"_id": "41343580|None", "id": "41343580", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "PLoS One;2025; 20 (12) 0338571. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0338571", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "PMC12677536", "type": "title", "authors": "Jantarawong S, Khimmaktong W, Panichayupakaranant P, Pengjam Y, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "CRE-Ter enhances murine bone differentiation, improves muscle cell atrophy, and increases irisin expression.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "murine", "locations": [{"offset": 17, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019042", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019042"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019042", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscle Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscle_Neoplasms"}, "text": "muscle", "locations": [{"offset": 55, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001284", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001284"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001284", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Atrophy"}, "text": "atrophy", "locations": [{"offset": 67, "length": 7}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 109, "text": "Ternary complex of curcuminoid-rich extract (CRE-Ter) is a developed water-soluble Curcuma longa extract containing 14% w/w curcuminoids, hydroxypropyl-beta-cyclodextrin, and polyvinylpyrrolidone K30. This study aimed to investigate the biomolecular effects of CRE-Ter on differentiation of bone cells (murine MC3T3-E1 preosteoblasts), muscle cells (murine dexamethasone-treated C2C12 myotubes) atrophy and irisin expression. In MC3T3-E1 preosteoblasts, CRE-Ter treatment increased alkaline phosphatase activity, calcium deposition, and expression of Bmp-2, Runx2, and collagen 1a significantly and dose-dependently. 5, 10, and 20 microg/mL CRE-Ter upregulated beta-catenin expression significantly. CRE-Ter improved the atrophy of dexamethasone-treated C2C12 myotubes. CRE-Ter decreased proinflammatory cytokine (TNF-alpha and IL-6) expression but increased FNDC5 and irisin expression and nitric oxide production in dexamethasone-treated C2C12 myotubes significantly and dose-dependently. Dexamethasone promoted beta-catenin and total p38 expression in C2C12 myotubes. CRE-Ter at 2.5-20 microg/mL reversed the increase in beta-catenin expression, whereas 2.5 microg/mL reversed total p38 expression. Crosstalk experiments further revealed that conditioned medium from C2C12 myotubes enhanced osteocalcin expression in MC3T3-E1 osteoblasts. Molecular docking simulations using CB-Dock2 showed strong interactions between each curcuminoid molecule and irisin. Therefore, CRE-Ter may stimulate osteoblast differentiation, ameliorate myotube atrophy, and increase irisin expression, indicating its therapeutic potential in osteoporosis, sarcopenia, and osteosarcopenia.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "50", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D036381", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D036381"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D036381", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Diarylheptanoids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Diarylheptanoids"}, "text": "curcuminoid", "locations": [{"offset": 128, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "51", "infons": {"identifier": "136217", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [136217], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 136217, "biotype": "species", "name": "136217", "accession": null}, "text": "Curcuma longa", "locations": [{"offset": 192, "length": 13}]}, {"id": "52", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D036381", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D036381"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D036381", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Diarylheptanoids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Diarylheptanoids"}, "text": "curcuminoids", "locations": [{"offset": 233, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "53", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D000073738", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D000073738"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D000073738", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "2-Hydroxypropyl-beta-cyclodextrin", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_2_Hydroxypropyl_beta_cyclodextrin"}, "text": "hydroxypropyl-beta-cyclodextrin", "locations": [{"offset": 247, "length": 31}]}, {"id": "54", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "polyvinylpyrrolidone K30", "locations": [{"offset": 284, "length": 24}]}, {"id": "55", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "murine", "locations": [{"offset": 412, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "56", "infons": {"identifier": "CVCL:0409", "type": "CellLine", "valid": true, "normalized": ["0409"], "database": "cvcl", "normalized_id": "0409", "biotype": "cellline", "name": "0409", "accession": null}, "text": "MC3T3-E1", "locations": [{"offset": 419, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "57", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019042", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019042"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019042", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscle Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscle_Neoplasms"}, "text": "muscle", "locations": [{"offset": 445, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "58", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "murine", "locations": [{"offset": 459, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "59", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D003907", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D003907"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D003907", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Dexamethasone", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Dexamethasone"}, "text": "dexamethasone", "locations": [{"offset": 466, "length": 13}]}, {"id": "60", "infons": {"identifier": "CVCL:0188", "type": "CellLine", "valid": true, "normalized": ["0188"], "database": "cvcl", "normalized_id": "0188", "biotype": "cellline", "name": "0188", "accession": null}, "text": "C2C12 myotubes", "locations": [{"offset": 488, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "61", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D001284", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D001284"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D001284", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Atrophy"}, "text": "atrophy", "locations": [{"offset": 504, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "62", "infons": {"identifier": "CVCL:0409", "type": "CellLine", "valid": true, "normalized": ["0409"], "database": "cvcl", "normalized_id": "0409", "biotype": "cellline", "name": "0409", "accession": null}, "text": "MC3T3-E1", "locations": [{"offset": 538, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "63", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002118", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002118"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002118", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Calcium", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Calcium"}, "text": "calcium", "locations": [{"offset": 622, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "64", "infons": {"identifier": "12156", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "926", "valid": true, "normalized": [12156], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 12156, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Bmp2", "accession": "@GENE_BMP2"}, "text": "Bmp-2", "locations": [{"offset": 660, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "65", "infons": {"identifier": "12393", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "68389", "valid": true, "normalized": [12393], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 12393, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Runx2", "accession": "@GENE_RUNX2"}, "text": "Runx2", "locations": [{"offset": 667, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "66", "infons": {"identifier": "12387", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "1434", "valid": true, "normalized": [12387], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id":