", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D019807", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019807"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019807", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Iodoacetic Acid", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Iodoacetic_Acid"}, "role2": {"identifier": "MESH:D020370", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D020370"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D020370", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Osteoarthritis Knee", "accession": "@DISEASE_Osteoarthritis_Knee"}, "type": "Positive_Correlation"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "3", "role": "13,40"}]}, {"id": "R5", "infons": {"score": "0.9978", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D007249"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D007249", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Inflammation", "accession": "@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, "role2": {"identifier": "24835", "type": "Gene", "valid": true, "normalized": [24835], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 24835, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Tnf", "accession": "@GENE_TNF"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "4", "role": "42,36"}]}], "pmid": 40800728, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-07-29T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Front Physiol", "authors": ["Duan Z", "Gao H", "Xiao X", "He B"], "relations_display": [{"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Inflammation|@GENE_IL1B"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Inflammation|@GENE_IL6"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Inflammation|@GENE_IL18"}, {"name": "cause|@CHEMICAL_Iodoacetic_Acid|@DISEASE_Osteoarthritis_Knee"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Inflammation|@GENE_TNF"}]}, {"_id": "40810394|None", "id": "40810394", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "J Cachexia Sarcopenia Muscle;2025Aug; 16 (4) 70045. doi:10.1002/jcsm.70045", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "PMC12351639", "type": "title", "authors": "Park S, Shin MK, Jeong DS, Yeo XY, Kim YJ, Muhammad J, Kim M, Gu S, Lee JE, Park Y, Lim SB, Mun JY, Jung S, Lee DR, Jo J, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Human Pluripotent Stem Cell-Derived Skeletal Muscle Organoid Model of Aging-Induced Sarcopenia.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "Human", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "Sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 84, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 96, "text": "BACKGROUND: Sarcopenia is defined by the age-related loss of muscle mass and function, with an impaired regenerative capacity of satellite cells (SCs). Despite their recognized importance in muscle regeneration, human model-based studies on SCs in sarcopenia are still lacking, limiting our understanding of their role in age-related muscle loss. Here, we aimed to develop a sarcopenia model using human pluripotent stem cells (hPSCs)-derived skeletal muscle organoids (hSkMOs) and prevent the sarcopenia progression by testosterone treatment. METHODS: The 3D hSkMOs were generated from hPSC and exhibited structurally and functionally mature muscle fibres and spinal-derived neurons including motor neurons and interneurons. The proportion of muscle and the diameter of muscle fibres were assessed. To investigate the acute pro-inflammatory response and intrinsic regenerative capacity of hSkMOs, we induced sarcopenia-like conditions by TNF-alpha treatment for 2 days and analysed. To model aging-induced sarcopenia and investigate the preventive effect of testosterone, chronic TNF-alpha treatment was applied, followed by testosterone administration. Histological, biochemical, molecular and electrophysiological analyses were conducted in various experiments. RESULT: We employed a stepwise differentiation protocol from 2D paraxial mesodermal induction to 3D myogenic specification, concluding with a maturation culture system. We observed that the majority of cells were T/BRA- and TBX6-positive (+) paraxial mesodermal progenitors (T/BRA+, 82.04%; TBX6+, 78.18%), whereas the neuromesodermal progenitors demonstrated a relatively low proportion (T/BRA+/SOX2+, 15.91%; TBX6+/SOX2+, 11.45%). Single-nucleus RNA-sequencing and extensive immunohistochemistry confirmed the presence of the myogenic lineage cell types (myogenic progenitors/SCs, myocytes, muscle fibres) and the neural lineage cell types (spinal-derived interneurons, motor neurons, glial cells, Schwann cells). Additionally, the growth of MyHC+ muscle fibres reached twice the thickness on Day 100 compared to that on Day 50 (p < 0.0001). We subjected them to TNF-alpha treatment and analysed. Western blot analysis confirmed that TNF-alpha/NF-kappaB pathway associated factors such as NF-kappaB p65, IkappaB-alpha and AKT were highly phosphorylated (p < 0.05, p < 0.001). The administration of testosterone increased the proportion of activated SCs (PAX7+/MYOD+, 7.97%; PAX7+/Ki67+, 7.03%) compared to the TNF-alpha group (PAX7+/MYOD+, 2.29%; PAX7+/Ki67+, 2.07%, p < 0.001). The administration of testosterone increased the Cross-Sectional-Area (987.1 mum2) compared to the TNF-alpha group (644.7 mum2, p < 0.01). CONCLUSIONS: We successfully developed a hSkMOs to demonstrate the structural maturity of the skeletal muscle and its functional interaction with spinal-derived interneurons and motor neurons. Furthermore, we demonstrated that our hSkMOs are useful for modelling aging-induced sarcopenia and providing a valuable platform for testing therapeutic interventions.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "44", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "Sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 108, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "45", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019588", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019588"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019588", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Aging Premature", "accession": "@DISEASE_Aging_Premature"}, "text": "age", "locations": [{"offset": 137, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "46", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 308, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "47", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 344, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "48", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D019588", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D019588"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D019588", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Aging Premature", "accession": "@DISEASE_Aging_Premature"}, "text": "age", "locations": [{"offset": 418, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "49", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009135", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009135"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009135", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Diseases"}, "text": "muscle loss", "locations": [{"offset": 430, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "50", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 471, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "51", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "human", "locations": [{"offset": 494, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "52", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 590, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "53", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D013739", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D013739"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D013739", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Testosterone", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Testosterone"}, "text": "testosterone", "locations": [{"offset": 616, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "54", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D007249", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D007249"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D007249", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Inflammation", "accession": "@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, "text": "inflammatory", "locations": [{"offset": 925, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "55", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D055948"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D055948", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Sarcopenia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Sarcopenia"}, "text": "sarcopenia", "locations": [{"offset": 1005, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "56", "infons": {"identifier": "7124", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "496", "valid": true, "normalized": [7124], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 7124, "biotype": "gene", "name": "TNF", "accession": "@GENE_TNF"}, "text": "TNF-alpha", "locations": [{"offset": 1035, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "57", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D055948", "