, "normalized_id": 4790, "biotype": "gene", "name": "NFKB1", "accession": "@GENE_NFKB1"}, "type": "Negative_Correlation"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "1", "role": "15,18"}]}, {"id": "R3", "infons": {"score": "0.9993", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D020155", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D020155"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D020155", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "3-Hydroxybutyric Acid", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_3_Hydroxybutyric_Acid"}, "role2": {"identifier": "114548", "type": "Gene", "valid": true, "normalized": [114548], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 114548, "biotype": "gene", "name": "DFNA34", "accession": "@GENE_DFNA34"}, "type": "Negative_Correlation"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "2", "role": "15,19"}]}], "pmid": 41201763, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-11-07T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Pharmacol Rep", "authors": ["Pokora B", "Pokora K", "Binienda A", "Fichna J"], "relations_display": [{"name": "treat|@CHEMICAL_3_Hydroxybutyric_Acid|@DISEASE_Inflammation"}, {"name": "negative_correlate|@CHEMICAL_3_Hydroxybutyric_Acid|@GENE_NFKB1"}, {"name": "negative_correlate|@CHEMICAL_3_Hydroxybutyric_Acid|@GENE_DFNA34"}]}, {"_id": "41219902|None", "id": "41219902", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Biomark Res;2025Nov11; 13 (1) 145. doi:10.1186/s40364-025-00855-2", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "PMC12607215", "type": "title", "authors": "Wang Y, Zhang M, Liu J, Li C, Sun N, Wu X, Wang C, Tan X, Yang Y, Qi X, Zhang Y, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Novel therapeutic strategies for targeting fatty acid oxidation in cancer.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005227", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005227"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005227", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Fatty Acids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids"}, "text": "fatty acid", "locations": [{"offset": 43, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "cancer", "locations": [{"offset": 67, "length": 6}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 75, "text": "Metabolic rewiring is a defining feature of malignant cells, enabling them to dynamically exploit nutrient resources to meet bioenergetic problems at different growth stages. Beyond the classical Warburg effect, recent studies have shown that neoplasms demonstrate a marked dependency on lipid metabolism, using free fatty acids to support cellular proliferation and regeneration via fatty acid oxidation (FAO). As a central component of lipid metabolism, FAO exerts dual immunomodulatory functions within tumors. Although numerous studies have described the enzymatic reactions of the FAO pathway in different malignancies, relatively few have investigated the pharmacological disruption of these enzymatic checkpoints and the resulting immunological consequences. Moreover, existing therapeutic strategies have failed to achieve a risk-benefit balance, limiting the clinical translation of FAO-directed approaches. To better understand the therapeutic implications of FAO, we investigated the mechanistic pathways mediated by mitochondrial rate-limiting enzymes, with a particular focus on the carnitine palmitoyltransferase 1 enzyme family-the critical gatekeeper controlling the entry of fatty acids into mitochondrial oxidation instead of CPT2. We comprehensively evaluated its role in tumor biology and also highlight future research directions to inform rational intervention strategies.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "neoplasms", "locations": [{"offset": 318, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008055", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008055"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008055", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Lipids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Lipids"}, "text": "lipid", "locations": [{"offset": 363, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005230", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005230"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005230", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Fatty Acids Nonesterified", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids_Nonesterified"}, "text": "free fatty acids", "locations": [{"offset": 387, "length": 16}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005227", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005227"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005227", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Fatty Acids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids"}, "text": "fatty acid", "locations": [{"offset": 459, "length": 10}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008055", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008055"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008055", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Lipids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Lipids"}, "text": "lipid", "locations": [{"offset": 513, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "tumors", "locations": [{"offset": 581, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "20", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "malignancies", "locations": [{"offset": 686, "length": 12}]}, {"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D005227", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005227"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005227", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Fatty Acids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids"}, "text": "fatty acids", "locations": [{"offset": 1267, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "1376", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "77", "valid": true, "normalized": [1376], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 1376, "biotype": "gene", "name": "CPT2", "accession": "@GENE_CPT2"}, "text": "CPT2", "locations": [{"offset": 1319, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "tumor", "locations": [{"offset": 1366, "length": 5}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [{"id": "R1", "infons": {"score": "0.9977", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D005227", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005227"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005227", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Fatty Acids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids"}, "role2": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "0", "role": "9,11"}]}, {"id": "R2", "infons": {"score": "0.9987", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D008055", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008055"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008055", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Lipids", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Lipids"}, "role2": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "1", "role": "6,11"}]}, {"id": "R3", "infons": {"score": "0.7015", "role1": {"identifier": "MESH:D005230", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D005230"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D005230", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Fatty Acids Nonesterified", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids_Nonesterified"}, "role2": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "type": "Association"}, "nodes": [{"refid": "2", "role": "4,11"}]}], "pmid": 41219902, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-11-11T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Biomark Res", "authors": ["Wang Y", "Zhang M", "Liu J", "Li C", "Sun N", "Wu X", "Wang C", "Tan X", "Yang Y", "Qi X", "Zhang Y"], "relations_display": [{"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Lipids|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, {"name": "associate|@CHEMICAL_Fatty_Acids_Nonesterified|@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}]}, {"_id": "41224958|None", "id": "41224958", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Nat Metab;2025Nov12. doi:10.1038/s42255-025-01397-5", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "11059056", "type": "title", "authors": "Angelino E, Bodo L, Sartori R, Malacarne V, D'Anna B, Formaggio N, Barua S, Raiteri T, Lauria A, Reano S, Murabito A, Nicolau M, Ferrero F, Pezzini C, Rossino G, Favero F, Valmasoni M, Filigheddu N, Menga A, Cor&#xe0; D, Hirsch E, Oliviero S, Sartorelli V, Proserpio V, Ghigo A, Sandri M, Porporato PE, Talarico D, Caretti G, Graziani A, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Impaired cAMP-PKA-CREB1 signalling drives mitochondrial dysfunction in skeletal muscle during cancer cachexia.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "-", "type": "Chemical", "valid": false, "normalized_id": null, "biotype": "chemical"}, "text": "cAMP", "locations": [{"offset": 9, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "1385", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3223", "valid": true, "normalized": [1385], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 1385, "biotype": "gene", "name": "CREB1", "accession": "@GENE_CREB1"}, "text": "CREB1", "locations": [{"offset": 18, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "6", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D028361", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D028361"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D028361", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Mitochondrial Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Mitochondrial_Diseases"}, "text": "mitochondrial dysfunction", "locations": [{"offset": 42, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "7", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "cancer cachexia", "locations": [{"offset": 94, "length": 15}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 111, "text": "Skeletal muscle wasting is a defining feature of cancer cachexia, a multifactorial syndrome that drastically compromises patient quality of life and treatment outcomes. Mitochondrial dysfunction is a major contributor to skeletal muscle wasting in cancer cachexia, yet the upstream molecular drivers remain elusive. Here we show that cancer impairs the activity of cAMP-dependent protein kinase A (PKA) and of its transcriptional effector CREB1 in skeletal muscle, ultimately contributing to the downregulation of a core transcriptional network that supports mitochondrial integrity and function. The restoration of cAMP-PKA-CREB1 signalling through pharmacological inhibition of the cAMP-hydrolysing phosphodiesterase 4 (PDE4) rescues the expression of mitochondrial-related genes, improves mitochondrial function and mitigates skeletal muscle wasting in male mice. Altogether, our data identify tumour-induced suppression of the cAMP-PKA-CREB1 axis as a central mechanism contributing to mitochondrial dysfunction in skeletal muscle during cancer cachexia. Furthermore, these findings highlight PDE4, particularly the PDE4D isoform, as a potential therapeutic target to preserve muscle mitochondrial function and counteract muscle wasting in cancer cachexia.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009133", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009133"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009133", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy"}, "text": "muscle wasting", "locations": [{"offset": 120, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009369", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009369"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009369", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Neoplasms", "accession": "@DISEASE_Neoplasms"}, "text": "cancer cachexia", "locations": [{"offset": 160, "length": 15}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "9606", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [9606], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 9606, "biotype": "species", "name": "9606", "accession": null}, "text": "patient", "locations": [{"offset": 232, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D028361", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D028361"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D028361", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Mitochondrial Diseases", "accession": "@DISEASE_Mitochondrial_Diseases"}, "text": "Mitochondrial dysfunction", "locations": [{"offset": 280, "length": 25}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009133", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D009133"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D009133", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Muscular Atrophy", "accession": "@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy"}, 