", "Ghigo A", "Sandri M", "Porporato PE", "Talarico D", "Caretti G", "Graziani A"], "relations_display": [{"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy|@GENE_CREB1"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy|@GENE_PDE4A"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Muscular_Atrophy|@GENE_PDE4D"}, {"name": "associate|@GENE_CREB1|@GENE_PDE4A"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Mitochondrial_Diseases|@GENE_CREB1"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Neoplasms|@GENE_PDE4D"}, {"name": "inhibit|@DISEASE_Neoplasms|@GENE_CREB1"}, {"name": "associate|@DISEASE_Neoplasms|@GENE_PDE4A"}]}, {"_id": "41231334|None", "id": "41231334", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Biogerontology;2025Nov13; 26 (6) 203. doi:10.1007/s10522-025-10349-1", "year": "2025", "article-id_pmc": "9486566", "type": "title", "authors": "Sayed SMA, Pitas A, Schmitz-Linneweber C, Saul N, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Transcriptomic insights into the healthspan-enhancing effects of C. chinensis seed and E. ulmoides bark extracts in Caenorhabditis elegans.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "4392", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [4392], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 4392, "biotype": "species", "name": "4392", "accession": null}, "text": "E. ulmoides", "locations": [{"offset": 87, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "6239", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [6239], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 6239, "biotype": "species", "name": "6239", "accession": null}, "text": "Caenorhabditis elegans", "locations": [{"offset": 116, "length": 22}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 140, "text": "Healthspan, the disease-free period of life, has become a central focus in aging research. Cuscuta chinensis seed and Eucommia ulmoides bark extracts, two traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) remedies, have shown promising healthspan-extending effects in Caenorhabditis elegans. In this study, RNA-seq analysis of aged worms treated with these extracts revealed significant transcriptomic alterations. Gene ontology and KEGG pathway analyses indicated upregulation of genes involved in immune defense, lysosomal function, and protein homeostasis, which may underlie the shared phenotype of enhanced stress resistance and lifespan extension. Beyond these effects, C. chinensis further improved multiple health parameters. Consistent with its broad spectrum of phenotypes, C. chinensis induced extensive transcriptomic remodeling involving over 3000 differentially expressed genes. Modulating collagen-, unc-, and muscle-related genes may explain improved locomotion, while upregulation of mec genes could contribute to enhanced mechanosensation. Notably, far-3, encoding a fatty acid- and retinol-binding protein, was upregulated more than 150-fold, and RNA interference assays demonstrated that FAR-3 is necessary for C. chinensis-induced healthspan improvement. Furthermore, C. chinensis influenced genes linked to antagonistic pleiotropy and insulin-like signaling, suggesting a systemic, hormesis-driven reprogramming of aging processes. Together, these findings uncover both shared and distinct molecular mechanisms through which C. chinensis and E. ulmoides promote healthspan in C. elegans.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "12", "infons": {"identifier": "267557", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [267557], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 267557, "biotype": "species", "name": "267557", "accession": null}, "text": "Cuscuta chinensis", "locations": [{"offset": 231, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "13", "infons": {"identifier": "4392", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [4392], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 4392, "biotype": "species", "name": "4392", "accession": null}, "text": "Eucommia ulmoides", "locations": [{"offset": 258, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "14", "infons": {"identifier": "6239", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [6239], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 6239, "biotype": "species", "name": "6239", "accession": null}, "text": "Caenorhabditis elegans", "locations": [{"offset": 393, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "15", "infons": {"identifier": "186127", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "76719", "valid": true, "normalized": [186127], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 186127, "biotype": "gene", "name": "col-64", "accession": "@GENE_COL_64"}, "text": "collagen", "locations": [{"offset": 1029, "length": 8}]}, {"id": "16", "infons": {"identifier": "179785", "type": "Gene", "valid": true, "normalized": [179785], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 179785, "biotype": "gene", "name": "far-3", "accession": "@GENE_FAR_3"}, "text": "far-3", "locations": [{"offset": 1192, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "17", "infons": {"identifier": "179785", "type": "Gene", "valid": true, "normalized": [179785], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 179785, "biotype": "gene", "name": "far-3", "accession": "@GENE_FAR_3"}, "text": "FAR-3", "locations": [{"offset": 1333, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "18", "infons": {"identifier": "4392", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [4392], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 4392, "biotype": "species", "name": "4392", "accession": null}, "text": "E. ulmoides", "locations": [{"offset": 1689, "length": 11}]}, {"id": "19", "infons": {"identifier": "328850", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [328850], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 328850, "biotype": "species", "name": "328850", "accession": null}, "text": "C. elegans", "locations": [{"offset": 1723, "length": 10}]}], "relations": []}], "relations": [], "pmid": 41231334, "pmcid": null, "meta": {}, "date": "2025-11-13T00:00:00Z", "journal": "Biogerontology", "authors": ["Sayed SMA", "Pitas A", "Schmitz-Linneweber C", "Saul N"], "relations_display": []}, {"_id": "41253741|None", "id": "41253741", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Aging Cell;2025Nov18 70294. doi:10.1111/acel.70294", "year": "2025", "type": "title", "authors": "Ikeda K, Shiba S, Yokoyama M, Fujimoto M, Horie K, Tanaka T, Inoue S, "}, "offset": 0, "text": "Mitochondrial Respiratory Supercomplex Assembly Factor COX7RP Contributes to Lifespan Extension in Mice.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "20463", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3463", "valid": true, "normalized": [20463], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 20463, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Cox7a2l", "accession": "@GENE_COX7A2L"}, "text": "COX7RP", "locations": [{"offset": 55, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "Mice", "locations": [{"offset": 99, "length": 4}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 105, "text": "COX7RP is a critical factor that assembles mitochondrial respiratory chain complexes into supercomplexes, which is considered to modulate energy production efficiency. Whether COX7RP contributes to metabolic homeostasis and lifespan remains elusive. We here observed that COX7RP-transgenic (COX7RP-Tg) mice exhibit a phenotype characterized by a significant extension of lifespan. In addition, metabolic alterations were observed in COX7RP-Tg mice, including lower blood glucose levels at 120 min during the glucose tolerance test (GTT) without a significant difference in the area under the curve (AUC), as well as reduced serum triglyceride (TG) and total cholesterol (TC) levels. Moreover, COX7RP-Tg mice exhibited elevated ATP and nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide levels, reduced ROS production, and decreased senescence-associated beta-galactosidase levels. Single-nucleus RNA-sequencing (snRNA-seq) revealed that senescence-associated secretory phenotype genes were downregulated in old COX7RP-Tg white adipose tissue (WAT) compared with old WT WAT, particularly in adipocytes. This study provides a clue to the role of mitochondrial respiratory supercomplex assembly factor COX7RP in resistance to aging and longevity extension.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "20463", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3463", "valid": true, "normalized": [20463], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 20463, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Cox7a2l", "accession": "@GENE_COX7A2L"}, "text": "COX7RP", "locations": [{"offset": 105, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "26", "infons": {"identifier": "20463", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3463", "valid": true, "normalized": [20463], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 20463, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Cox7a2l", "accession": "@GENE_COX7A2L"}, "text": "COX7RP", "locations": [{"offset": 281, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "20463", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3463", "valid": true, "normalized": [20463], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 20463, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Cox7a2l", "accession": "@GENE_COX7A2L"}, "text": "COX7RP", "locations": [{"offset": 377, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "20463", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3463", "valid": true, "normalized": [20463], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 20463, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Cox7a2l", "accession": "@GENE_COX7A2L"}, "text": "COX7RP", "locations": [{"offset": 396, "length": 6}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "10090", "type": "Species", "valid": true, "normalized": [10090], "database": "ncbi_taxonomy", "normalized_id": 10090, "biotype": "species", "name": "10090", "accession": null}, "text": "mice", "locations": [{"offset": 407, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "20463", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "3463", "valid": true, "normalized": [20463], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 20463, "biotype": "gene", "name": "Cox7a2l", "acce